commit.message:
Bump version to 1.8.7

Fixes performance issues with larger torrent files.
Merge branch 'performance'

Make the program much quicker.

Seems that modifying a member with an in-place list section a lot of
times kills the performance. Instead we simply keep the whole file in
memory and keep track of how much of the string we have already taken.
Add Python 3.3 testing to Travis. Closes #13.
Put the program name in the license header.
Travis notifications
Update the README as well.
Update repository URL.
Add a build status images to the README
Fix a small mistake in docs.
Drop tests support for Python <2.6
Don't check error code for Python <2.6.
Update version to v1.8.6.
Merge branch 'issue12'
Throw a bogus UnknownTypeChar exception when the file is empty. Fixes #12.
Update the test to assert the exit code and clean stdout.
Test for empty file.
Merge branch 'issue11'

Handle unicode files containing unicode in them correctly. Fixes #11.

We now take the stream as either bytes or string and let the string buffer
worry about converting between the two when necessary.
Add a test for a file containing unicode characters.
Add a torrent with a file unicode file.
Merge branch 'issue9'
Print comment by default, even if not present. Closes issue #9.
Test the comment showing up properly when it's present.
Update tests with empty comment line.
Revert to symlink creation. Hopefully this finally fixes the issues.
